lyrics:

Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods

They're gonna crumble one by one
Then we gon' ride right into the sun
Like it's the day my kingdom come
Baby, we're

[Post-Chorus: Hyein]
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods
Yeah, we're
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods

Is it your name in the rafters?

And they're singin' my praises, la-la-la

This is why we're immortal now 'cause

I'm on my knees, pray for glory
Anyone read this underdog story?
I can't lose myself again
Help me raise this heart
Heart, unbreakable

[Chorus: Haerin, Hanni, Minji, Danielle]
Once you play God, once you play God
They're gonna crumble one by one (Crumble one by one)
Then we gon' ride right into the sun
Like it's the day my kingdom come
Once you play God, once you play God
They're gonna crumble one by one

Like it's the day my kingdom come
Baby, we're

[Post-Chorus: Hyein, Haerin]
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods
Yeah, we're (Gods)
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods
Yeah, we're (Gods)
Go-Go-Go-Go-Go-Gods

[Outro: Danielle]
Once you play
imageDescription: A golden spotlight shines on a microphone standing on a stage. The background is filled with a vibrant mix of red, purple, and orange lights, creating a celestial atmosphere. In the center, a crown made of shining stars hovers above the microphone, symbolizing the power and immortality of the gods.
